- GameApp (in app.py): Orchestrates the GUI application, handles the Pygame loop, renders board and UI, processes text-input moves, displays status and errors, and manages game restarts.
- Board (in board.py): Represents the 8x8 board, holds pieces, initializes starting positions, provides movement operations, and draws the board and pieces.
- Piece (in board.py): Represents a single checker piece with color and king status.
- GameState (in rules.py): Implements checkers rules: generating legal moves, forced captures, executing moves (including multiple jumps), kinging, and detecting game over.
- MoveParser (in move_parser.py): Parses user-entered move notation (e.g., "b6-c5" or "c3:e5:g7") into coordinate sequences.
- InputBox (in ui.py): Text-input component for Pygame to allow users to type their moves.
- constants (in constants.py): Shared configuration for board size, colors, fonts, and geometry.

Key functions and methods:
- GameApp.run(): Main loop to process events, render, and tick the clock.
- GameApp.handle_move_input(text): Parse and attempt to apply a move based on user input, update status or show errors.
- Board.setup_initial(): Place 12 pieces for each player on dark squares of rows 0-2 (black) and 5-7 (red).
- Board.draw(surface, font, last_move): Renders squares, pieces, and last move highlight.
- GameState.get_legal_moves(player): Generates all legal moves, enforcing mandatory captures.
- GameState.apply_move(seq): Applies a validated move sequence (handles captures and kinging).
- GameState.is_game_over(): Checks if a player has no legal moves or pieces.
- MoveParser.parse(text): Converts a string like "b6-d5-f4" to a list of (row, col) coordinates.
- InputBox.handle_event(event): Updates internal text from key presses and toggles activation on mouse click.
- InputBox.draw(surface): Renders the input box and current text.

